So its been.... 3 or 4 months since my last update, so I'll fill you all in on whats been going down. I'm 20 now, I've been driving a bit... will hopefully have my license soon, but I'm not going to get my hopes up. Sinapse has been playin some shows and making new friends. Our purevolume site (www.purevolume.com/sinapse) has over 1000 profile views, so I guess were not doin to bad. We got played on a few college radio stations and are working on shows in a few different parts of the state and are trying to get some in canada. August 13th (my birthday) we played up in port huron at a Rubyfest and... well I dont remember many of the details, but we stayed the night (it was 2 days long) and partied with SM and some other new friends most of the night. And then this last sunday I went camping for 3 days with Greg, Aaron and his cousin Steven. Kelli and Brad came up on the 2nd day. Some crazy stuff happened there, like on the first night, we went hiking and were hearing crazy tribal drums through alot of the trail. It was like we were being chased by Indians. I think the last time I updated was right around the time I moved in with Greg... We'll thats been going pretty good, better then I could have hoped for actually. Sure me and greg get in little fights and stuff, but theyre more like brotherly fights now so... yeah... thats that. Well I know it was a kind of short update and I probably left out alot of stuff that happened in the last few months but.... I get bored reading those entries that cover ever damn detail of someones day and... well writing them is even worse so... I bid you all farewell

havent been online really since I moved, should have internet hooked up sometime this weekend, hope to talk to you all then.

Well tonight Sinapse played at the roseville theater, and let me tell you, it was AWESOME. We had a total of 42 tickets come in so we got, $42... sucks considering it was an $8 ticket but whatever. 8 more people and we would have gotten a big $75. Anyway, thank you to EVERYONE who came out to see us, it was a blast and I dont think anybody will understand the amount of happiness being on stage brings me. We have atleast 2 more shows schedualed, both at the roseville theatre again. Saturday January 15th, we play at 10:30 and Febuary 5th at the battle of the bands, as of right now were playing at 3:30 for that but theyre trying to give us alittle bit later of a time slot so I'll keep you all updated on that. We also might be playing a show in chicago early next month and a battle of the bands at the irock in detroit. Once again thank you to all who came out tonight, even if you didnt like the music or didnt even plan on liking and just came out to support a friend, thank you!

So, 2 updates in under a week, who woulda thought!  Yesterday was turkeyfest, and it... to say the least, kicked ass.  We finally got the 'first show' out of the way and are working on setting up atleast 2 more next month.  I'd like to thank everyone who watched us and showed support, it was such an awesome feeling. Today I'm 19.  I feel so old, like when I think of somebody thats 19, I'm like wow... theyre old.  Last night some of us stayed at alex's for the night and it was lots of fun, today were supposed to practice but chris is still working so I dont know, tomorrow I'm hopin for practice but dont know, sunday is warped tour, then monday were gunna try to practice early and THEN

SHADOWS FALL IN GRAND RAPIDS!!!

I can't think of the last time I was this excited for a show, its been awhile, and then tuesday is Ozzfest, which will also be alot of fun.

My dad just called while I was typing that last little part, first time I've talked to him in like 5 years and I didn't even realize it was him until the conversation was almost done, I didnt really recognize his voice and was just thinking who the hell is this crazy guy talking to me?!

anyway I don't really have any train of thought right now and intended to write alot more in here but I can't really think of what else there was right now so I'll just leave with saying I love my friends, both new and old, theyre the reason I'm alive

So I decided maybe I will update this journal some... but it will only be the same as my deadjournal, so heres what I wrote in there:

This situation seems so familiar... but so much more complicated.  Should I just say whatever I dont care anymore and let things take its course?  I wish I could but... I care to much to do that and would only feel worse if I did.... but at the same time its almost humiliating how I deal with it because there doesnt seem to be any other way besides just saying whatever and not trying anymore... which as previously stated I cant do because I care to much, but I'm afraid I cant carry on how I am now much longer because everytime anything happens it just makes me want to die.... alwell, I'll just have to get over it, besides.. as I recently figured out... I will be alone for the rest of my life, but atleast I still have my music

Aren't you tired of being weak?
Such rage that you could scream. all the stars right out of the sky 
And destroy the prettiest starry night. every evening that I die. alone

on a happier note, I'm going to see The Darkness and it may end up being one of the greatest shows ever, I cant wait, also as I lay dying saturday and poison the well next week.
